### User:
How do you align a row of divs to the right using flex in css?  Show me an example.

### Response:


To center a single element horizontally and vertically, use `display:flex` on its parent container with properties set as follows:

```css
parent {
  display: flex; /* enables flexible box layout */
  justify-content: space-between; /* aligns items along main axis (horizonal) */
  align-items: center; /* centers item vertically within the cross axis*/ 
} 

/* or if you want to right align instead of between, use `justify-content` property with value 'flex-end'
parent {
  display: flex; 
  justify-content: flex-end;  
  align-items: center;  
}

```
